There are a couple of relevant files in our group&#39;s Resources directory:
http://groups.yahoo.com/group/Read_Alphabet/files/Resources/

1) Jon Zuck proposed the revised letter names in &quot;Second Shaw.htm&quot;. I
see three tiny mistakes in your chart: he has #12 as &#39;Zoos&#39;, #29 as
&#39;Age&#39;, and #35 as &#39;Oil&#39;.

2) The rationale for the keyboard layout (also by Jon Zuck) is in &quot;QS
Keyboard Driver Remapping.htm&quot;.

I find the first document compelling. I haven&#39;t studied the second one
in detail. For some time I&#39;ve wanted to come up with another keyboard
layout. I&#39;d like to see all of the QS letters mapped to lower and
upper case Latin letters. Tossing out some of the mappings for
ligatures and half-letters, we could use &#39;W&#39; for #20 and &#39;L&#39; for #42,
for example. I&#39;m undecided whether to suggest &#39;x&#39; and &#39;X&#39; for #43 and
#44, as a look at X-SAMPA suggests that &#39;x&#39; would be good for #41. But
then I suppose a careful attempt to come up with single ASCII
characters to correspond to the 44 QS symbols based on X-SAMPA might
be difficult. I haven&#39;t tried yet.

Googling around a bit, I found a couple of other interesting ASCII
phonetic mappings, such as ENgliS:
http://foolswisdom.com/users/sbett/ENgliS.htm

And also Kirshenbaum notation: http://www.kirshenbaum.net/IPA/

Is there anyone else who&#39;d like to see changes in the keyboard mappings?

Ted


